# Security and permissions {% #security-and-permissions %}

Security guidance is grouped at two levels: project configuration (sessions, API keys, MFA policy, password rules, JWT usage) and end-user protections (password hashing, transport security, rate limits, and platform-layer abuse defenses).

[Authentication security](/docs/products/auth/security) covers product-specific controls and recommendations. [Security](/docs/advanced/security) covers compliance, encryption, TLS, audit logging, and broader platform posture.

Authorization for [Databases](/docs/products/databases) and [Storage](/docs/products/storage) uses the same scope vocabulary as Authentication: `user`, `team`, `role`, and `public`. Team and membership scopes apply to organization-scoped data. [Labels](/docs/products/auth/labels) support tags and coarse roles referenced from rules without hard-coding user identifiers in application logic.
